Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Melt butter or margarine over low heat. Stir together all ingredients, including butter or margarine, and mix well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place them about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Press flat with thumb. Bake for 9 minutes or until edges are golden. Cool on cookie sheets one minute. Remove to wire racks to cool.